{% capture default_body_html %}
  <h2>Stage And Availability</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>Can I buy it now?</summary>
    <p>No. This preview is notify-only for now, so pricing and checkout are not live.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Is this a live launch page or a preorder page?</summary>
    <p>No. The site is in product-preview mode, so the frontstage surface only shows the object, the current boundaries, and the update sign-up.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Can I join a preorder or waitlist?</summary>
    <p>No. There is no preorder, waitlist, or reservation mechanic in this stage.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Why are price, inventory, and shipping timing not shown?</summary>
    <p>Sample review is still pending, so live commerce details stay offstage until the review-backed version is ready.</p>
  </details>

  <h2>Product Facts</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>Is this the silver-lined version?</summary>
    <p>No. This preview is for the non-silver-lined version.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>How many products does this page represent?</summary>
    <p>One product only. The current preview does not branch into multiple versions, capacities, or bundles.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Are the images final product photos?</summary>
    <p>No. The page uses reference imagery or placeholders until review-backed photography is ready.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Are the specs final?</summary>
    <p>Not yet. The current dimensions are shown as catalog-listed details and remain pending sample review.</p>
  </details>

  <h2>Updates And Privacy</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>What is my email used for?</summary>
    <p>Your email is used for updates on this product only. It does not create a reservation or purchase commitment, and you can unsubscribe later.</p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Why keep a sign-up form if the product is not live yet?</summary>
    <p>Because updates are the only low-commitment action the preview should support right now. It helps measure interest without creating a transaction promise.</p>
  </details>
{% endcapture %}

{% capture aside_html %}
  <span class="preview-doc__tag">FAQ</span>
  <span class="preview-doc__tag">Notify Only</span>
  <p>If you want to move through the preview surface in order, use these entry points:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/pages/preview-stage">Preview Terms</a></li>
    <li><a href="/pages/copper-kettle-preview">Product Details</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ routes.root_url }}">Home</a></li>
  </ul>
{% endcapture %}

{% render 'preview-page-shell',
  eyebrow: 'Frequently Asked Questions',
  title: 'Questions We Can Answer Now',
  intro: 'These answers cover the current preview surface only. Final launch details will be added after sample review, not before.',
  page_title: page.title,
  page_content: page.content,
  body_html: default_body_html,
  aside_title: 'Preview Paths',
  aside_html: aside_html,
  cta_title: 'Need the actual product surface next?',
  cta_text: 'The product details page applies the same boundaries inside the single-product preview layout and keeps the sign-up live.',
  cta_label: 'View Product Details',
  cta_link: '/pages/copper-kettle-preview'
%}
